        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Interstitial granulomatous dermatitis with arthritis is a rare rheumatologic disease characterized by the occurrence of inflammatory arthritis in association with large erythematous symmetrical cutaneous lesions (ranging from typical but infrequent cord-like lesions on the flanks to more common violaceous plaques on the trunk and limbs) featuring a typical histologic infiltrate mainly constituted of histiocytes."
        },
